Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a new control strategy for a differential drive mobile robot, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control of a nonlinear system with disturbances and uncertainties, which is a core topic in systems and control. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses an Active Disturbance Rejection Control (ADRC) strategy, which is a machine learning-based control technique. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an improved version of the ADRC strategy, which involves the estimation and cancellation of disturbances, a common problem in AI-based control. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses digital simulations to evaluate the performance of the proposed control strategy, which falls under the domain of computational engineering.
